sentences: Miori Takimoto (瀧本 美織, Takimoto Miori, born October 16, 1991) is a Japanese actress and a former singer.
Takimoto debuted in 2003 as a singer of the girl group Sweets, where she performed under the name Miori.
She was chosen from the avex trax 2002–2003 auditions, and the group debuted on August 27, 2003.

During these years, she had side projects such as modelling for magazines and acting in Waseda Academy commercials.
Miori and her fellow ex-SweetS members parted ways on June 7, 2006.
She appeared in a music video for Himari in November 2007.
In November 2014, she debuted with the band Lagoon (ラグーン) as the vocalist.
